Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Public health focuses on the wellbeing of the population and consequently may come into conflict with the interests of each individual. With vaccine preventable diseases, this conflict of interest has become all too common. Individuals may need to sacrifice a little freedom of choice to meet the needs of the greater good. The approach to decrease the size of outbreaks of measles suggested in this report, i.e., by making request for an exemption more labor-intensive, could be successful unless parents are adamantly opposed to the practice of vaccination. In that case, education is the best path to effect a change so parents understand the consequences of refusal to vaccinate. - Mod.LK]
